{
  "text": "Recent studies suggested that inhibition of GSK-3\u2424 leads to cardiomyocyte hypertrophy. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Myocytes that were transfected with a mutant GSK-3\u2424, which could not be phosphorylated, did not undergo hypertrophy. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Hypertrophy is initially a compensatory mechanism, and although prolonged hypertrophy is associated with heart failure, the exact relationship between signals that activate hypertrophy and those that activate failure are not clearly delineated. Thus, the protective effects of GSK-3\u2424 inhibition are not necessarily inconsistent with stimulation of hypertrophy. It is also possible that short-term activation of GSK-3\u2424 is protective whereas long-term activation may have other detrimental effects.",
